# Autonomous Agent Guide: Building IcePhone on Next.js 15 & Cloudflare Workers

## Welcome to IcePhone Development

You're building **IcePhone** - an AI-powered CRM and Voice Agent Platform that helps business owners set up custom Voice Agents for inbound calls, outbound cold calls, and autonomous follow-ups. This guide will walk you through implementing features systematically with a focus on quality and incremental development.

**Environment Configuration**: Your development variables are in `.dev.vars`

## 🎯 Getting Started: Check the Master Plan

Before implementing ANY feature, always start here:

```bash
# Check what features are planned and their current status
cat docs/MASTER_FEATURES_CHECKLIST.md

# See if your feature is already in progress
grep -i "{feature-name}" docs/MASTER_FEATURES_CHECKLIST.md
```

The master checklist contains:

- All 25 planned features with priorities
- Current implementation status
- Dependencies between features
- Quarterly implementation roadmap

**Important**: If a feature exists in the checklist, follow its existing roadmap. If not, add it first before starting implementation.

## ✅ Checklist Management: Track Your Progress

As you work on any feature, you MUST maintain two critical checklists that track development progress:

### 1. Master Features Checklist (`docs/MASTER_FEATURES_CHECKLIST.md`)

This is the high-level project roadmap containing all 25 planned features. Update it to reflect:

- ✅ **Started**: When you begin working on a feature
- 🚧 **In Progress**: When development is actively happening
- ✅ **Complete**: Only when the entire feature is implemented AND tested

### 2. Feature-Specific Checklists (`docs/features/{feature-name}/checklist.md`)

Each feature has its own detailed checklist breaking down all subtasks required for completion. This includes:

- Database schema changes
- Server actions implementation
- UI components creation
- Authentication integration
- Error handling
- Mobile responsiveness
- Performance optimization
- Comprehensive testing

### Critical Checklist Rules

**🔄 Update Continuously**: As you complete each subtask, update the feature-specific checklist immediately. This provides visibility into progress and helps identify blockers early.

**⏳ Don't Mark Complete Prematurely**: Only mark a feature as "Complete" in the master checklist when:

1. ✅ ALL subtasks in the feature checklist are done
2. ✅ ALL tests pass (unit, integration, e2e)
3. ✅ Feature works end-to-end in development environment
4. ✅ Code review checklist items verified
5. ✅ Performance benchmarks met
6. ✅ Security validation completed

**📝 Document Blockers**: If you encounter issues or dependencies, immediately update the checklist with:

- What the blocker is
- Why it's blocking progress
- What needs to happen to resolve it
- Any alternative approaches being considered

### Checklist Update Commands

```bash
# View current master status
cat docs/MASTER_FEATURES_CHECKLIST.md

# View specific feature progress
cat docs/features/voice-agents/checklist.md

# Update feature progress (example)
echo "- [x] Database schema created" >> docs/features/voice-agents/checklist.md
echo "- [ ] Server actions implemented" >> docs/features/voice-agents/checklist.md
```

**Remember**: Checklists are not just documentation—they're your roadmap to systematic, high-quality feature delivery. Keep them current, accurate, and detailed.

